features: Style Home: Equipped with woven rattan, while angled legs and golden handles, the drawer dresser will add a mid-century charming to your home. Use on its own or pair it with other rattan matching pieces from Airbuyhome

Multi-Purpose: NOT only a dresser, it can also be used as beside tabe, TV stand(suit for 50"TV), clothing organizer/lingerie dresser, entryway table, accent storage cabinet for living room. Ideal for bedroom, closet, living room and entryway

Easy to Assemble: Due to the simple design, labled accessories and detailed instructions, it only takes about 40 minutes with 2 person, you can get a practical 6 drawer dresser

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Size and Beautiful
reviews.reviewText: Sturdiness: 7/10 but looks beautiful, does its job. The laminate material deteriorates easily because I left my essential oils on the dresser and it seeped through. Was able to fix it but definitely be careful. Took a long time to build but I love it, just be sure to put the drawers on the right side. Love the detailing. Matches all my other furniture (:

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Stunning but AT WHAT COST
reviews.reviewText: Great chest of drawers. Very pretty! With that said, it’s worth saying - I build furniture all the time, I am IKEA-level-expert. BUT sweet lord this dresser took me TEN HOURS TO BUILD. The instructions are not super clear, just pictures. I thought I would be fine with this (thank you IKEA!) but refer to the 10 hours part. So not okay.it great but, prepare yourself.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Very pretty dresser
reviews.reviewText: Very nice dresser but not the easiest to assemble as there are way too many pieces. It took about 4 hours to put together. Its not a heavy duty piece but it does the job and it looks as pictured but i am disappointed in the quality of this product. Its very cheap and the drawers are too light. They dont shut well and dont hold heavy items.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It’s cute, but not my fave
reviews.reviewText: I love the look of this dresser in every way. It was a bit time consuming to put together but it’s not hard at all if you follow the instructions!My only complaint is that it probably won’t last more than a year. I already have to be pretty careful with opening and closing the drawers just right so they don’t get stuck. I think for a guest room, this item is great but for a main bedroom where you’re using it everyday - not the best idea.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Iw ent with the 8 drawer size instead of 6 because I know this type of furniture usually runs a little bit smaller than normal furniture, and I'm glad I did. The price is great, it was easy to build, but it is not real wood, of course. It's in our guest room so it won't be used much, so I think we'll get more use out of it than someone who would use it everyday. But, I do feel like it was a sturdy build so should last others a good while as well. I was very impressed with the packaging, nothing was damaged at all in the delivery process.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and not difficult to put together
reviews.reviewText: I took a gamble on this as there weren't a ton of reviews. I am so happy with it! We got it for the nursery. It is HEAVY in the box. But my husband got it up the stairs on his own. Took him a few hours to put together with all the pieces but it was easy.For those saying the drawers don't line up, read the instructions. My husband thought the same thing but the drawers have a certain side they go on, not all interchangeable.It was left in the rain in our driveway all day, the box was soaked. But nothing was ruined!!Haven't added anything to it, but I think for little baby clothes it will work perfectly. We plan to add a changing table on top. We aren't too tall, I'm 5'2" and my husband is 5'8" so I don't think it's too short for us.The drawers open and close easy but are not "quiet" like I've seen other dressers say. There are spots to hook it to the wall so it doesn't fall.Overall I'd definitely recommend this! It feels good quality so think it should last, even if it gets us a few years for our little one it will be worth it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This dresser is great especially for the price. It was a lot to put it together, but easy instructions/manual to follow. It looks so beautiful, awesome quality. 10/10 would recommend.
